The paper discusses performance modeling of distributed-memory parallel codes, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses wave pattern formation, which is a topic in Pattern Formation and Solitons (cs.PF). The use of microbenchmarks and Chebyshev filter diagonalization also suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS) and Applied Mathematics (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the dynamics of communication and computation, which could fall under the category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
